$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Numerator} &= P(\text{Test +} \mid \text{Disease}) \times P(\text{Disease}) \\
&= 0.90 \times 0.01 \\
&= 0.009
\end{aligned}
$$



I still have to write things out or draw pictures to help me keep this straight. And this is the right approach. Here's a simple way to think about it:

The key question: Which tail do you want?

         |-------------X------------|
         lower tail    4    upper tail
         (left)             (right)

lower.tail = TRUE → gives you P(X ≤ 4) — everything to the LEFT of (and including) 4
lower.tail = FALSE → gives you P(X > 4) — everything to the RIGHT of 4

Quick rule:

If your question has "less than" or "at most" → lower.tail = TRUE
If your question has "greater than" or "at least" → lower.tail = FALSE

For "at least 5" = "X ≥ 5" = "X > 4" → we want the upper (right) tail → lower.tail = FALSE
So: ppois(q = 4, lambda = 3, lower.tail = FALSE) gives P(X > 4) which equals P(X ≥ 5).